President Cyril Ramaphosa made the declaration following the death of the anti-apartheid icon on Monday. JOHANNESBURG - Winnie Madikizela-Mandela will have an official national funeral. President Cyril Ramaphosa made the declaration following the death of the anti-apartheid icon on Monday. Madikizela-Mandela passed away on Monday afternoon at the Milpark Hospital surrounded by her family. The struggle stalwart had been in and out of the facility, battling a recurring kidney infection. A national memorial service will be held on 11 April and the funeral will be held on 14 April. WATCH: Ramaphosa pays tribute to Winnie Madikizela-Mandela 